text.tspan: This is probably the most common usage for the pathbar: a filter with autocompletion. This moves the
awkwardly placed filter from the bottom corner of Nautilus into a location that makes sense. You can see
that the icon has changed to an arrow to communicate that Marlin recognizes "~/Music" as a valid path.
Of course, you can manually type in a path and Marlin will recognize this as well. Any "/" character that
occurs before your entered text will automatically be converted to a ">" graphic. This is to maintain
consistent spacing when the pathbar moves from breadcrumb to edit mode. You will not see the text shift.
This is a secure website. You can see that by the lock icon where a normal favicon would show. In keeping
with the panel, a monochrome urlbar is a happy urlbar.
This website is insecure. We've stated this with a red lock icon.
